Package uk.ac.ucl.cs.gc01.restaurant_billing_system.objects

Provides the classes necessary to represent the different objects that form the restaurant in order to build the system.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DigitalClock
    The DigitalClock class generates a Label which displays a live clock.
    Employee
    The Employee class used to generate the employees for our restaurant It provides a template for the Manager class.
    FoodItem
    The FoodItem class represents the different FoodItems on the menu.
    Manager
    The Manager class allows to distinguish a manager from an employee.
    OrderDetails
    The OrderDetails class represents the different details contained in an order.
    OrderItems
    The OrderItems class represents the different details contained in an order as well as the details about the items in those orders.
    Table
    The Table class represents the different details that a Table can store.

Package uk.ac.ucl.cs.gc01.restaurant_billing_system.objects Description

Provides the classes necessary to represent the different objects that form the restaurant in order to build the system. They provide handles to pass the between the database and the GUI (e.g. populating Table Views).

Author:
Miguel Marin Vermelho
